(43, 8, 33, 16, 5, 4, 8, 'Ye shall be made free', 'Bondage and Freedom Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bondage, with Nehemiah addressing the physical bondage of the Jewish people and John discussing a spiritual freedom. This connection highlights the struggle against oppression and the desire for liberation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 33, 16, 9, 27, 28, 'never in bondage to any man', 'Bondage and Deliverance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bondage and deliverance. In John 8:33, the claim of never being in bondage contrasts with Nehemiah 9:27-28, which recounts Israel''s repeated experiences of oppression and divine rescue.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 33, 2, 1, 13, 14, 'never in bondage to any man', 'Bondage and Freedom Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of bondage and freedom. In John 8:33, the claim of never being in bondage contrasts with the historical reality of the Israelites'' hard bondage in Exodus 1:13-14.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 33, 3, 25, 42, 42, 'Ye shall be made free', 'Freedom and Bondage Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of freedom from bondage. John 8:33 mentions being ''made free,'' while Leviticus 25:42 emphasizes that God''s servants should not be sold as bondmen, indicating a divine intention for freedom.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 45, 6, 16, 16, 'servant of sin', 'Servants of Sin and Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of servitude to sin. John 8:34 states that those who commit sin are ''the servant of sin,'' while Romans 6:16 discusses yielding oneself as a servant to whom one obeys, linking sin to death.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 61, 2, 19, 19, 'servant of sin', 'Servants of Sin and Corruption', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being a servant to sin or corruption. John 8:34 states that those who commit sin are the ''servant of sin,'' while 2 Peter 2:19 describes individuals as ''servants of corruption.'' This connection highlights the bondage that comes from yielding to sin.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 20, 5, 22, 22, 'servant of sin', 'Servitude to Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of sin, illustrating how individuals become bound by their own iniquities. John 8:34 states that committing sin makes one a servant of sin, while Proverbs 5:22 describes the wicked being held by the cords of their sins.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 62, 3, 8, 10, 'Whosoever committeth sin', 'Connection Between Sin and Servitude', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between sin and one''s identity. John 8:34 states that those who commit sin are servants of sin, while 1 John 3:8-10 indicates that those who commit sin are of the devil, highlighting a similar theme of servitude to sin and its consequences.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 45, 6, 6, 6, 'servant of sin', 'Servitude to Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of serving sin. John 8:34 states that those who commit sin are the servants of sin, while Romans 6:6 discusses the destruction of the body of sin to prevent serving sin.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 56, 3, 3, 3, 'servant of sin', 'Connection of Sin and Servitude', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of servitude to sin and desires. John 8:34 states that committing sin makes one a servant of sin, while Titus 3:3 describes serving divers lusts and pleasures, illustrating the bondage to sinful behaviors.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 34, 49, 2, 2, 2, 'servant of sin', 'Servitude to Sin and Disobedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of servitude, as both passages discuss the consequences of sin and disobedience. John 8:34 states that those who commit sin are servants of sin, while Ephesians 2:2 refers to those who walk in disobedience under the influence of a negative spiritual power.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 48, 4, 4, 7, 'the Son abideth ever', 'Servants and Sons in Christ', 'This connection highlights the transition from being a servant to becoming a son. Both passages emphasize the permanence of the Son''s position and the believer''s new identity as an heir through Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 42, 15, 31, 31, 'the Son abideth ever', 'Connection of Sonship and Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the enduring presence of the Son. In John, the Son abides forever, while in Luke, the Son is described as always being with the father.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 1, 21, 10, 10, 'the Son abideth ever', 'Inheritance and Permanence', 'This connection highlights the theme of permanence in relation to inheritance. In John 8:35, the Son''s eternal status contrasts with the bondwoman''s son, who is excluded from the inheritance in Genesis 21:10.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 45, 8, 15, 17, 'the Son abideth ever', 'Sonship and Inheritance', 'Both passages emphasize the status of believers as children of God. John highlights the permanence of the Son''s position, while Romans speaks of believers as heirs with Christ, indicating a shared relationship with the Son.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 48, 4, 30, 31, 'the Son abideth ever', 'Connection of Sons and Inheritance', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the son and the servant. The servant''s lack of permanence contrasts with the son’s enduring status, paralleling the theme of inheritance between the bondwoman''s son and the freewoman''s son.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 26, 46, 17, 17, 'the servant abideth not in the house for ever', 'Servants and Inheritance', 'This connection highlights the distinction between servants and sons in terms of permanence and inheritance. John emphasizes that the Son abides forever, while Ezekiel notes that a servant''s inheritance is temporary, returning to the prince after a set time.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 35, 58, 3, 5, 6, 'the servant abideth not in the house for ever', 'Servant and Son Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between a servant and a son within a household. John highlights that the servant does not remain forever, while Hebrews affirms Christ''s eternal role as a son over His house.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 47, 3, 17, 17, 'free indeed', 'Freedom in Christ and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of freedom. John 8:36 speaks of being made free by the Son, while 2 Corinthians 3:17 states that where the Spirit is, there is liberty.', 'theme', 0.909, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 48, 5, 1, 1, 'make you free', 'Freedom in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom granted by Christ. John 8:36 states that the Son makes one free, while Galatians 5:1 encourages believers to stand firm in that freedom.', 'theme', 0.8109999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 45, 8, 2, 2, 'free indeed', 'Freedom in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom. John 8:36 speaks of freedom granted by the Son, while Romans 8:2 describes freedom from the law of sin and death through Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.727, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 43, 8, 31, 32, 'free indeed', 'Freedom Through Truth and Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom. John 8:31-32 states that knowing the truth leads to freedom, while John 8:36 affirms that the Son makes one free, linking truth and freedom to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 42, 4, 18, 18, 'free indeed', 'Freedom and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom and deliverance. John 8:36 speaks of being made free, while Luke 4:18 mentions delivering captives and setting at liberty those who are bruised.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 38, 9, 11, 12, 'free indeed', 'Freedom and Deliverance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of freedom found in both passages. John 8:36 speaks of being made free by the Son, while Zechariah 9:11-12 refers to prisoners being released from a pit, emphasizing liberation and hope.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 36, 23, 61, 1, 1, 'free indeed', 'Connection of Freedom and Liberty', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom. John 8:36 speaks of being made free by the Son, while Isaiah 61:1 proclaims liberty to the captives, highlighting a shared message of deliverance.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 37, 43, 8, 45, 47, 'my word hath no place in you', 'Connection of Belief and Lineage', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between belief and being of God. In John 8:37, Jesus identifies his audience as Abraham''s seed, yet they do not accept his word. Similarly, in John 8:45-47, he states that those who are of God hear God''s words, indicating a disconnect between lineage and true belief.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 37, 46, 2, 14, 14, 'my word hath no place in you', 'Spiritual Discernment and Rejection', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual understanding and rejection. Both passages emphasize that those who are not spiritually attuned, like the ''natural man,'' cannot accept the truth of God''s word, as seen in the rejection of Jesus by those who are ''Abraham’s seed.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 37, 45, 9, 7, 7, 'Abraham’s seed', 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being Abraham''s seed. John 8:37 indicates a distinction between physical descent and spiritual acceptance, while Romans 9:7 clarifies that not all descendants of Abraham are considered children of God, highlighting a deeper meaning of lineage.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 37, 43, 7, 1, 1, 'ye seek to kill me', 'Connection of Hostility Towards Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the hostility of the Jews towards Jesus, highlighting their intent to kill him. John 8:37 indicates their rejection of his word, while John 7:1 notes their desire to kill him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 37, 44, 13, 26, 26, 'Abraham’s seed', 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'This connection highlights the identity of Abraham''s descendants in both passages. John 8:37 refers to those as ''Abraham’s seed,'' while Acts 13:26 addresses ''children of the stock of Abraham,'' emphasizing their shared heritage.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
